TetonCampsiteProject
results.snippet: We use the weighted overlay tool to take  reclassifies rasters for 25% views, 45% slope, and 30% distance from trails into mathmatical calculation. Its aim is to consider three factors mentioned above to compute an overall campsite suitability.The raster data generated from weighted overlay three raster data (reclassifies raster for views, slope, and distance from trails). The weighted overlay is based on the VALUE field in attribute table. VALUE are ranked in four levels, in which value 1 means unusable for campsite, value 2 is okay for campsite, value 3 is good for campsite and value 4 is best for campsite. Only consider three factor (views, slope, and distance from trails) that influencing the campsite suitability.
